* Bug Fix

  * Due to randomly picking between replicas and primaries for readonly
    commands when ``read_from_replicas`` was ``True`` - new connections for a slot
    that ended up using a primary instead of a replica could have had the
    ``READONLY`` command sent which would result in that connection being
    unusable for write commands. This change also effectively discludes
    primaries from readonly commands when ``read_from_replicas`` is set to
    True which is what the user probably expects to happen.
